f:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BLUR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's connection to NFT marketplace activity creates funding rate patterns that often diverge from broader crypto market trends, providing arbitrage opportunities independent of Bitcoin correlation. The token's lower liquidity on Bluefin compared to major CEXs can lead to sustained funding rate premiums during NFT trading surges."}]]}]
10:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR funding rates on Bluefin exhibit high volatility correlated with NFT market cycles, often spiking above +0.5% hourly during major collection launches or marketplace updates. The token shows distinctive weekend patterns where funding rates tend to normalize as NFT trading volume decreases. Unlike major tokens, BLUR rates can maintain sustained positive or negative bias for days during trending NFT events. The Sui ecosystem's early stage means BLUR often trades at premiums to other chains, creating consistent arbitrage opportunities for cross-chain traders. Rate spikes above +1% hourly have occurred during major Blur airdrop announcements or marketplace feature releases."}]]}]
11:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Exchange Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's BLUR rates frequently diverge from Binance and OKX due to the Sui ecosystem's isolation and lower overall liquidity. The hourly funding frequency provides more granular arbitrage opportunities compared to the 8-hour cycles on major CEXs. Arbitrageurs can exploit rate differentials by shorting on Bluefin during high positive rates while longing on exchanges with lower rates. The fast Sui settlement times enable efficient position adjustments, though bridge delays to other ecosystems limit some strategies. Rate differentials of 0.1-0.3% hourly are common during NFT market volatility, providing consistent profit opportunities for sophisticated traders."}]]}]
12:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's low liquidity on Bluefin creates significant slippage risks during large position entries or exits, particularly during funding payment windows. The token's high correlation with NFT sentiment means funding rates can shift rapidly during market events, requiring tight risk management. Bridge risks between Sui and other ecosystems can trap capital during volatile periods when immediate position adjustments are needed. The DEX's order book model provides better price discovery than AMMs but still suffers from thin liquidity during off-hours. Smart contract risks on the relatively new Sui ecosystem add additional considerations compared to established CEX arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
13:["$","$L15",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bluefin update BLUR funding rates?","answer":"Bluefin calculates and applies BLUR funding rates every hour, with payments occurring at the top of each hour. This provides more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to the 8-hour cycles common on major centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes BLUR funding rates unique on Bluefin compared to other DEXs?","answer":"Bluefin's institutional-grade matching engine and Sui's fast finality enable more accurate funding rate calculations. The combination of BLUR's NFT market exposure and Bluefin's order book model creates funding patterns that differ significantly from AMM-based perpetual DEXs."},{"question":"Are there minimum position sizes for earning funding on BLUR/USDT?","answer":"Bluefin doesn't impose minimum position sizes for funding payments, but the 0.02% maker fee means very small positions may not be economical. Positions should typically exceed $1000 to make funding rate arbitrage viable after accounting for trading fees."},{"question":"How do Sui network conditions affect BLUR funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"Sui's sub-second finality enables rapid position adjustments around funding windows, but network congestion during major NFT drops can delay transactions. The fast settlement generally favors funding rate strategies compared to slower networks, though bridge delays to other ecosystems can limit cross-chain arbitrage efficiency."}]}]
